quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,25,"We did send Noah unto his people, 'Verily, I am to you an obvious warner"
  11,26,"that ye should not worship any save God. Verily, I fear for you the torment of the grievous day"
  11,27,"But the chiefs of those who misbelieved amongst his people said, 'We only see in thee a mortal like ourselves; nor do we see that any follow thee except the reprobates amongst us by a rash judgment; nor do we see that you have any preference over us; nay more, we think you liars"
  11,28,"He said, 'O my people! let us see! if I stand upon a manifest sign from my Lord, and there come to me mercy from him, and ye are blinded to it; shall we force you to it while ye are averse therefrom"
  11,29,"O my people! I do, not ask you for wealth in return for it; my hire is only from God; nor do I repulse those who believe; verily, they shall meet their Lord. But I see you, a people who are ignorant"
  11,30,"O my people! who will help me against God, were I to repulse you? do ye not then mind"
  11,31,"I do not say that I have the treasures of God; nor do I know the unseen; nor do I say, \" Verily, I am an angel; \" nor do I say of those whom your eyes despise, \"God will never give them any good!\"- God knows best what is in their souls - verily, then should I be of the unjust"
  11,32,"They said, 'O Noah! thou hast wrangled with us, and hast multiplied wranglings with us; bring us then what thou hast threatened us with, if thou art of those who tell the truth"
  11,33,"Said he, 'God will only bring it on you if He pleases, nor can ye make Him helpless"
  11,34,"nor will my advice profit you, should I wish to advise you, if God wish to lead you into error. He is your Lord, and unto Him shall ye be returned"
  11,35,"Do they say, 'He has devised it? Say, 'If I have devised it, then on me be my sin. But I am clear of that wherein ye sin"